statements: SELECT * FROM population_health_data WHERE age > 50;
SELECT patient_id, medical_condition FROM population_health_data WHERE gender = 'female';
SELECT location, insurance_status FROM population_health_data WHERE medical_condition = 'diabetes' ORDER BY insurance_status DESC;
SELECT gender, COUNT(*) AS total_count FROM population_health_data GROUP BY gender;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_patients FROM population_health_data;
SELECT * FROM population_health_data WHERE age > 30 ORDER BY age DESC
SELECT gender, COUNT(*) FROM population_health_data GROUP BY gender
SELECT * FROM population_health_data WHERE medical_condition LIKE '%diabetes%' AND location = 'City A'
SELECT patient_id, age, insurance_status FROM population_health_data WHERE gender = 'Female' ORDER BY age ASC
SELECT * FROM population_health_data WHERE insurance_status = 'Uninsured' LIMIT 10
SELECT * FROM population_health_data;
SELECT patient_id, age, gender FROM population_health_data ORDER BY age DESC;
SELECT * FROM healthcare_services WHERE cost > 100;
SELECT provider_name, service_type FROM healthcare_services ORDER BY provider_name ASC;
SELECT * FROM population_health_data WHERE diagnosis_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
SELECT patient_id, age, gender, health_condition, diagnosis_date FROM population_health_data WHERE age > 30 ORDER BY age DESC
SELECT provider_name, service_type, location, cost FROM healthcare_services WHERE cost > 1000 ORDER BY cost ASC
SELECT * FROM healthcare_services WHERE location = 'New York' OR location = 'Los Angeles'
SELECT patient_id, gender, health_condition, age FROM population_health_data WHERE diagnosis_date BETWEEN '2021-01-01' AND '2021-06-30'
SELECT COUNT(*) AS Total_Patients, AVG(age) AS Average_Age FROM population_health_data
SELECT * FROM population_health_data;
SELECT city, state, avg_life_expectancy FROM population_health_data WHERE avg_life_expectancy > 75;
SELECT facility_name, location, type FROM healthcare_facilities WHERE type = 'Hospital';
SELECT trend_name, trend_description, impact_level FROM health_trends WHERE population_impacted > 10000;
SELECT city, population_size FROM population_health_data ORDER BY population_size DESC;
SELECT * FROM population_health_data ORDER BY city DESC, state ASC LIMIT 10;
SELECT city, state, population_size FROM population_health_data WHERE avg_income > 50000 ORDER BY population_size DESC;
SELECT city, avg_life_expectancy, avg_income FROM population_health_data WHERE avg_income BETWEEN 40000 AND 60000 AND avg_life_expectancy > 75 ORDER BY avg_life_expectancy DESC;
SELECT * FROM healthcare_facilities WHERE type = 'Hospital' AND services_provided LIKE '%Emergency%' ORDER BY facility_name ASC;
SELECT trend_name, trend_description, population_impacted FROM health_trends WHERE impact_level = 'High' ORDER BY population_impacted DESC, trend_name ASC LIMIT 5;
SELECT * FROM population_health_data ORDER BY county DESC;
SELECT state, life_expectancy FROM population_health_data WHERE population > 100000;
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM health_indicators WHERE year = 2021;
SELECT * FROM healthcare_facilities WHERE capacity >= 200 ORDER BY facility_name ASC;
SELECT provider_name, specialty, location FROM healthcare_providers WHERE location = 'New York';
SELECT * FROM population_health_data ORDER BY state DESC, county ASC
SELECT id, county, state, life_expectancy FROM population_health_data WHERE population > 500000 ORDER BY life_expectancy DESC
SELECT population, life_expectancy FROM population_health_data WHERE state = 'California' OR state = 'New York' AND county LIKE '%County%'
SELECT * FROM health_indicators WHERE year BETWEEN 2015 AND 2020 ORDER BY indicator_value DESC, indicator_name ASC

SELECT provider_name, specialty, location, contact FROM healthcare_providers WHERE location = 'Hospital A' OR location = 'Hospital B' AND specialty IN ('Cardiology', 'Pediatrics') ORDER BY provider_name ASC
SELECT * FROM healthcare_services;
SELECT provider_name, service_name FROM healthcare_services WHERE service_type='Hospital';
SELECT outcome_name, success_rate FROM health_outcomes ORDER BY success_rate DESC;
SELECT location, provider_type FROM healthcare_providers WHERE provider_type='Clinic' ORDER BY location;
SELECT provider_name, contact_number FROM healthcare_providers WHERE provider_type='Hospital' AND location='City A';
